[{'action': 'opened', 'author': 'sschuberth', 'comment_id': None, 'datetime': '2015-04-24 12:59:12+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_0', 'text': 'The example [To add multi-line PowerShell script covering an entire event](http://www.appveyor.com/docs/build-configuration) does not work for me. It says

    on_success: |
      if($true)
      {
        Write-Host "Success"
      }

But if done like this the code is executed as "cmd", not as "ps", and fails. I tried to guess the right syntax and used `on_success: ps |` in the first line which did not work either. After looking at [libgit2's appveyor.yml file](https://github.com/libgit2/libgit2/blob/master/appveyor.yml) I found that

    on_success:
      - ps: |
      if($true)
      {
        Write-Host "Success"
      }

works. It even works when adding other script lines before or after, very similar to the help page's next example that uses `- ps: >-`, but the above does not require the extra line breaks.

So I'm a bit confused. Why would I want to use `- ps: >-` if `- ps: |` works the same and does not require the extra line breaks?', 'title': 'Multi-line PowerShell script example is wrong', 'type': 'issue'}
